search::addTableField()

Description
    public null search::addTableField(string $tableID, string $fieldName [, string $label = NULL [, string $alias = NULL]])
    Adds an entry to $this->fields

Parameters
    tableID
        A string specifying the table's ID.

    fieldName
	A string containing a field name.

    label
	An optional variable containing the string for a label.

    alias
	Another optional string variable specifying an alias.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	// Add Fields
	// addTableField( tableID, fieldName, label, alias )
	$searchObj->addTableField($tableID['traditionalReserves'],"ID");
	$searchObj->addTableField($tableID['traditionalReserves'],"displayName","Name");
	...
    ?>

See Also
    search::addTableLink()
